<!--
  Moonshell — macOS hardened-runtime entitlements.

  Distribution model: Developer ID + notarization, NOT sandboxed (an SSH client
  must read ~/.ssh, arbitrary private-key files, and the Keychain — sandbox would
  break all three). Hardened runtime is applied by Tauri at signing time.

  Empty by design: network client, file reads, and own-Keychain access need no
  entitlement outside the sandbox. Add an exception below only if a future dependency
  requires it (e.g. com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation for a 3rd-party dylib).
-->
